{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id0cbc4947-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s1011"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1011"},"text":"§ 1011.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Antidiscrimination","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id0cbc4948-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s1011/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Institutions of higher education receiving Federal financial assistance may not use such financial assistance, directly or indirectly, to undertake any study or project or fulfill the terms of any contract containing an express or implied provision that any person or persons of a particular race, religion, sex, or national origin be barred from performing such study, project, or contract, except that nothing in this subsection shall be construed to prohibit an institution from conducting objective studies or projects concerning the nature, effects, or prevention of discrimination, or to have the institution’s curriculum restricted on the subject of discrimination.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id0cbc4949-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795","identifier":"/us/usc/t20/s1011/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Limitations on statutory construction","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Nothing in this chapter shall be construed to limit the rights or responsibilities of any individual under the Americans with Disabilities Act of 1990 [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s12101"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 12101","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], the Rehabilitation Act of 1973 ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s701"},"text":"29 U.S.C. 701","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], or any other law."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id0cbc494a-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/329/tI/s111"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–329, title I, § 111","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/244/tI/s101/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–244, title I, § 101(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-10-07"},"text":"Oct. 7, 1998","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/112/1590"},"text":"112 Stat. 1590","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/39/tI/s101/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–39, title I, § 101(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 2009","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/123/1935"},"text":"123 Stat. 1935","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id0cbc494b-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id0cbc494c-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id0cbc494d-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Americans with Disabilities Act of 1990, referred to in subsec. (b), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/336"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–336","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-07-26"},"text":"July 26, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/327"},"text":"104 Stat. 327","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to chapter 126 (§ 12101 et seq.) of Title 42, The Public Health and Welfare. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s12101"},"text":"section 12101 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Rehabilitation Act of 1973, referred to in subsec. (b), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/112"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–112","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-09-26"},"text":"Sept. 26, 1973","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/87/355"},"text":"87 Stat. 355","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to chapter 16 (§ 701 et seq.) of Title 29, Labor. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s701"},"text":"section 701 of Title 29","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"id0cbc494e-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Provisions similar to this section were contained in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t20/s1142"},"text":"section 1142 of this title","children":[],"tail":" prior to repeal by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/244"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–244","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 1011, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/329/tI/s121"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–329, title I, § 121","children":[],"tail"